**Problem 1.2** Show when implemented in floating point arithmetic for $A ∈ F^{m × n}$ and $𝐱 ∈ F^n$ that
$$
{\rm mul_rows}(A, 𝐱) = A 𝐱 + \mathbf{δ} 
$$
where
$$
\| δ \|_1 ≤ \|A\|_∞ \| 𝐱 \|_∞ E_{n-1,ϵ_{\rm m}/2}
$$
and
$$
E_{n,ε} := {n ε\over 1-nε},
$$
assuming that $n ϵ_{\rm m} < 2$. 
We use the notation (to be discussed in detail later):
$$
\|A \|_1 := \max_k ∑_{j=1}^n |a_{kj}|, \|𝐱\|_1 := ∑_{k=1}^n |x_k|. 
$$

**Proof**
Each entry of $mul_rows(A, 𝐱)$ is of the form 
$$
⨁_{j=1}^n A_{k,j} ⊗ x_j =  ⨁_{j=1}^n A_{k,j} x_j (1+δ_j) = 
∑_{j=1}^n A_{k,j} x_k (1+δ_j) + σ_n
$$
where
$$
M_k = Σ_{j=1}^n |A_{k,j}| |x_k| (1+δ_j) 
$$


